Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Cut the 
@tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Halve the @aubergine{1} lengthways, keeping the stem attached. Score the flesh in a criss-cross 
pattern, taking care not to cut through the skin.

Put the halves, cut-side up, onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{½%tsp} and season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until softened, 
~{25-28%minutes}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{120%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a 
#spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling 
raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the @harissa paste{50%g} and @tomato puree{30%g} into the pork. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water{100%ml}(for the sauce), stirring to combine.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce 
has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat the oil in a deep #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the garlic and cook 
for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{110%g} and cook until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water{220%ml}(for the bulgur), stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and bring 
to the boil. Simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or 
until ready to serve.

Once the aubergine has cooked, remove from the oven and preheat your #grill{} to high. Using 
a #tea towel{}, hold the stem of the roasted aubergine half with one hand, then use a spoon 
to gently scoop out the flesh whilst keeping the skin intact. Repeat for the other halves.

Roughly chop the aubergine flesh and add to a #medium bowl{} with the pork and @grated hard 
Italian style cheese{10%g}. Spoon the mixture back into each aubergine skin so all halves 
are filled.

Sprinkle over the remaining @grated hard Italian style cheese{10%g}, then grill until golden, 
~{3-5%minutes}.

When everything's nearly ready, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} 
and half the @mint{}.

Fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{} and stir through the tomato and remaining mint. Taste and 
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the bulgur between your bowls and top with the stuffed aubergine. Finish with a 
spoonful of mint yoghurt.

Enjoy!